:["Refer for new spectacles","Restrict activities","Eye patch","Oral antibiotics","Topical antibiotics"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe image shows detachment of the retina inferiorly and temporally and surrounding his macula, thus explaining his reduced vision. The patient also has a history of myopia (short-sightedness) which is a risk factor for retinal detachment. This patient requires prompt ophthalmological referral. Advice on \u003Cstrong\u003Erestricting his activities\u003C/strong\u003E until he sees an eye surgeon may lessen progression of his detachment.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EReferring him for new spectacles would delay the definitive retinal surgery he requires and make his visual outcome much worse. There is no indication for antibiotics nor patching.\u0026nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["A detached retina is an ophthalmological emergency, requiring prompt expert advice."],"references":["Bowling, B. (2015). Kanski\u2019s clinical ophthalmology (8th ed.). W B Saunders."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"19023"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"487"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"19492"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"19492","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19492"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/82a8477e-a3e9-455f-a2a8-d6395448e295.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/82a8477e-a3e9-455f-a2a8-d6395448e295.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":437}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"19023","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/19023"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2023-03-17T10:42:14+10:30","updatedAt":"2023-03-17T10:42:15+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"487"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"33689"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},